{
  "doc_id": "35287",
  "text": "However, a D-brane solution in matrix models does not come for free, it always carries a background gauge field F ij which is just the inverse of θ ij . Indeed for this solution, as first observed in [CITATION_1] , a noncommutative super Yang-Mills theory directly results from the matrix model. For the brane-anti-brane solution, there are different background gauge fields on D9-branes and anti-D9-branes. It is not known how to write down a simple field theory with an associative algebra generalizing the star product. On the D9-branes, the star product is defined with the noncommutative parameters θ ij , while on the anti-D9-branes, the star product is defined with −θ ij . If one naively generalizes the product to include both, one will not get an associative algebra.",
